      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Buenos Aires, 17 August 1871. ¶ Dear Sir: ¶ The phrasing of Olivera's letter is somewhat unusual. The text appears to be a poor translation of a letter written in English. The translation given here i...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">71.08.17c</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">From Eduardo Olivera</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found. For the text given here, see<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>'Semillas para Australia'<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>[Seeds for Australia]<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Anales de la Sociedad Rural Argentina</seg>, 1871, vol. 5, pp. 242-3.</p>
               </note>Buenos Aires, Agosto 17 de 1871.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Muy señor mio:</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A su debido tiempa fuí favorecido con sus apreciables cartas de 1.° de Enero y 10 de Febrero del corriente año. La primera acusando recibo de las semillas que esta Sociedad le mandó el año pasado, y la segunda avisando el envío á Lóndres para esta corporacion, de una coleccion de producciones vegetales ese país.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Despues de estas cartas he recibido aviso del señor D. Jorge Verdon, de haber embarcado dicho cajon con destino á esta Sociedad en el buque "Elisa" que todavía no ha llegado; y hoy le escribo diciéndole que en retribucion, esta Sociedad le manda otro cajon con semillas indígenas de esta República para que<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>se<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>sirva dirijirlo á vd.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Esta cajon va primeramente á nuestro Cónsul en Liverpool, D. Guillermo R. Gilmour para que lo mande al señor Verdon, y le hemos encargado que procure no sea abierto en la aduana á fin de que no sufran deterioro las semillas.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Va incluso<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>incluido?</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>el detalle de las semillas que le mandamos, y deseamos que sean de su agrado y de provecho para el pais.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>La lista de las que esperamos de vd. por el buque "Elias"<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Text footnote: 'Véase página 196 de los "Anales" del corriente año' [See page 196 of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Anales<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>for this year], i.e. M to the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Sociedad Rural Argentina</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">, 1 January 1871.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>nos inspiran mucho interés y sentimos no tener á mano algunas obras de vd. como "The Australian Vegetation" para poderlas apreciar debidamente, pero hoy mismo la pedimos á Inglaterra.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Suponiendo que vd. publica algunos estudios, boletin<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>ó<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>memoria sobre la vegetacion y agricultura de ese pais, mucho le estimaríamos nos lo hiciera conocer.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Me resta, señor, manifestar á vd. el alto aprecio con que le saluda la Sociedad Rural, que tengo el honor de presidir, y su muy atento S. S. Q. B. S. M.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">EDUARDO OLIVERA,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Presidente.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Jaime Arrufo</seg>.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Secretairio.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">P. D. — En el acto de recibir su última me dirijí al señor Presidente de la República, indagando sobre la carta y el cajon de semillas que vd. dice le mandó; pero desgraciadeamente no la recibió y el cajon debe haberse<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>perdido con ella, puesto que en vano le hemos buscado en toda la Aduana.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">OLIVERA.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Buenos Aires, 17 August 1871.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Dear Sir:</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The phrasing of Olivera's letter is somewhat unusual. The text appears to be a poor translation of a letter written in English. The translation given here is therefore a slightly free translation to convey the probable sense of the letter sent to M.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In due<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>course<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I was favored with<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>your<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>estimable<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>letters of January 1st and February 10th of this year. The first one acknowledging receipt of the seeds that this Society sent<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>you<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>last year, and the second<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>advising of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the shipment to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>London<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for this corporation<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of a collection of vegetable productions<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>[of]<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>your<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>country.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>After these le</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">tters I received advice from Mr</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>George Verdon,</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Victoria’s Agent-General in London.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of having shipped said box to this Society on the ship "Elisa"</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>that has not yet arrived</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">.</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">T</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">oday I write to you saying that in return, this Society sends<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">him</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>another box with indigenous seeds of this Republic so that<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">he</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">may</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>direct it to you.</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Anales</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>a letter to Verdon precedes the letter to M. The letter acknowledges the receipt of Verdon's letter of 16 June 1871 advising of the despatch of M's seeds per<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Elisa.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Olivera notifies Verdon that another box of seeds intended for M has been sent to the Argentine Consul in Liverpool, William Gilmour, together with the letter to M, and asks Verdon to arrange for them to be sent to M.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This box goes first to our Consul in Liverpool, William R. Gilmour, to send it to Mr<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Verdon, and we have instructed him to try to prevent opening in the customs so that the seeds do not suffer deterioration.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The detail of the seeds that we<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>are<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>sending<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>you is included, and we<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>hope<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>that they are<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>your liking and of benefit for the country.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">The list of what we expect from you<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">per "Elias" has ins</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">p</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">ired much interest,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">and we regret not having some of your works at hand</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">s</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">uch as</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>"The Australian Vegetation"</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Presumably B67.13.03 or one of the other versions of this article.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to be able to appreciate them properly, but today we ask</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">ed for</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>it<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">from</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>England.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Assuming you<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>publish<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>some studies, bulletins<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>or<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>notes<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>on the vegetation and agriculture of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>your<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>country, we should much<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>appreciate knowing of it.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">t</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>remain</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">s to me</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">, sir, to manifest to you the high appreciation with which the Rural Society,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">over<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">which I have the honor to preside,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">being</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>your very attentive S. S. Q. B. S. M</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">.</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn7" n="8">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A conventional valedictory phrase, 'seguro servidor que besa sus manos' [reliable servant who kisses your hand].</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">EDUARDO OLIVERA,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>President.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Jaime Arrufo</seg>.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Secretary.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Immediately on receiving your last I addressed the President of the Republic, inquiring about the letter and the box of seeds that you say you sent him; but<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">unfortunately he did not receive it and the box must have been lost with it, since we have looked for it i</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">n vain<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">i</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">n all the Customs.</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn8" n="9">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No letter mentioning the President of the Republic has been found.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
         </div>
